Wilmington.1995 LPGA Championship:
The 1995 LPGA Championship was the 41st LPGA Championship, played May 11–14 at DuPont Country Club in Wilmington, Delaware.
Kelly Robbins won her only major title, one stroke ahead of defending champion Laurie Davies. Robbins had led after each of the first two rounds, but fell a stroke behind leader Davies after 54 holes.
